              %p
                %strong
                  Adding a photo to the image library
              %p
                %a{:href => "http://www.concord.org/sites/all/themes/cc/flash/video/player.swf?skin=/sites/all/themes/cc/flash/video/skins/classic.swf&video=http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/projects/videos/itsisu/images.mov&autoplay=1&fullscreen=true", :target=>"_blank"} Click here to watch the video on 'Images'.

              %p
                To add an image into an activity you must have the URL of the image.  If you obtain an URL from the Internet it is possible that the image could move or the person hosting the image could take it down. To upload an image to the Image Library, save it to your computer.  Click on the Images link on the navigation bar.
              %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_image_library_link.png", :alt=>"Image Library Link"}
              %p
                This will bring you to the Image Library.
              %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_image_library.png", :alt=>"Image Library Screen Shot"}
              %p
                Click 
                %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_create_image.png", :alt=>"Create Image Button"}
                , found on the yellow bar above the images.  If your image is larger than the given dimensions (650 x 400), the image will automatically be resized to fit.  If the image is extremely large, you may resize it on your computer.  Name the image.  In the attribution box, enter the name of the author, “Creative Commons”, and the website where the photo was found.  For example, John Smith Creative Commons Flickr.  Choose the file from your computer, then click 
                %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_create.png", :alt=>"Create Button"} 
                The URL for embedding the image can be found below. 

              %p
                You can search for specific images or browse the entire library.  When browsing the image library, you can sort the images alphabetically by name or by date added.  To view the images that you have created, check the box labeled “Only Mine”.  

              %p
                %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_insert_image.jpg", :alt=>"Image Icon", :style=>"float: right; margin-left: 10px;"}
                To add an image click on 
                %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_edit.jpg", :alt=>"Edit"} 
                When the WYSIWYG box opens up look in the edit bar for a button that looks like a tree. 
                %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_treeimageinbar.jpg", :alt=>"Image Icon"} 
                &nbsp;Once you click on the 
                %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_treeimageinbar.jpg", :alt=>"Image Icon"} 
                &nbsp;you will be prompted for the URL of the image.
              %p
                Click the 
                %img{:src=>"http://www.concord.org/sites/default/files/images/projects/itsisu/itsisu_insert_green_button.jpg", :alt=>"Image Icon"} 
                &nbsp;when you have entered the URL to insert the photo.
              %p
                If you do not want the photo that is inserted simply delete the image with the delete key.
